			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Who are you, and why do you play in Molto Espressivo?<a name="56798"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 15 04 4:59 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><i>1. What was your EQ experience prior to joining Molto?</i>
<br />
Originally, I played a bard called Mozi on Veeshan.  I started around the release of Velious.  I was a member of a loose guild at first, and then a mid-level raiding guild.  I got tired of the game and quit, leaving my character and a guild that was farming the east wing of Temple of Veeshan just before PoP came out.
<br />

<br />
<i>2. Why did you join Molto? </i> 
<br />

<br />
I had stopped playing the game for several months, but I still frequented EQDiva's boards.  I saw Klapton's thread about starting a group of bards that would work and fight together, and it really got me interested.  A month later, Sony sent me an email, giving me a free month of play time in order to hook me back in, and it worked.  I created my new bard just after the guild was officially started.
<br />

<br />
<i>3. What are your favorite memories of Molto? </i> 
<br />

<br />
Wow... quite a few here, I'll list some of the most notable:
<br />
My first really great memory of Molto was of Pajaull helping me with my newby armor.  He was extremely generous with his time, and remains to this day one of the kindest people I've met.
<br />

<br />
My first true all-bard grouping experience was in Splitpaw, where as part of a 6-bard team (aka a rolling ball of death), we handled content that some groups 10 levels higher than us often struggled with.
<br />

<br />
Growing up as a guild often involves a lot of pooling of resources and time.  We brought it together in a big way to get ourselves some Thunderous Drums of Karana.  It was a frequent thing for everyone online to smash their savings to help buy a TDoK for a guildie.  The selflessness of the guild was frequently and redily tested, and we shined.  It was beautiful.
<br />

<br />
I have several fond memories of being part of a bard charm kite-team in Eastern Wastes in my 40's, and in Western Wastes in my early 50's.  One time, Pajaull and I teamed up and killed the big named mammoth there when we were both 52 (that's a level 63 mob).
<br />

<br />
Later, as I approached 60, I decided that I would go and get a Lute of the Howler in Velks.  I led 12 different groups down there.  The last one had 4 bards in it, and I had the distinct pleasure of winning it in the company of some very good friends.  
<br />

<br />
One of my most personally rewarding roles in the guild is being an armor smith.  When LDoN came out, the smithed armor that came with it helped my smithing career to take off, and a lot of bards in Molto continue to wear pieces I've smithed for them.  
<br />

<br />
My fondest memory, and greatest honor, was to be Molto's first epic bard.  In a sense, my epic is very much the guild's epic, as I had tons of help getting it done, and a number of people either gave me some of the quest pieces, or helped me camp them.  The culmination of the epic quest, the Trakanon raid, was a real breakthrough for me and for the guild, and the effort helped set the stage for a number of other Molto bards to get their own epics.  We even have some bards outside the guild asking for our help with their epic quest.
<br />

<br />
<i>4. What is your typical day in Molto like? </i> 
<br />

<br />
I raid a lot with AWNN, our high-level raid ally.  We do mostly PoP stuff.  When we're not raiding, I do a wide variety of things, from tradeskills to recruiting to grouping with alliance and guild members.  I try to vary my game up week to week.
<br />

<br />
<i>5. Any other comments you would have about your time in Molto are welcome. </i> 
<br />

<br />
I wouldn't be playing this game if it weren't for Molto Espressivo.  I've never heard of a guild that works like we do, and the experience and challenge of the guild has been terrific.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=601903">Feroce</a> <br> 
Battle Bard, Grandmaster Smith, and Tradeskill Officer of Molto Espressivo, the All-Bard Guild of Firiona Vie</span></td>
