<br />
4. What is your typical day in Molto like? 
<br />
Typical day is like this... try an AoE pull in dulak, get too close to the mob bundle, die.... ask advice to guild while doing my CR, recieve good advice and try again,  pull mob bundle, get a lag spike, die.... relay funny story to guild while doing CR #2.... try pull again , all goes well, mob bundle is down to 4% life, random monk_01 walks up to me watching in wonder, gets in my way, I bump into him , my circle is interupted just enough .... mobs kill me and then kill monk.... Random_monk_01 tells you WTF!
<br />
I splain to monk why he should form now on stay back from an aoe'ing bard from now on.  He understands and tells me he is sorry. I do CR #3, .... total exp lost so far = 1.75 yellow bubbles.
<br />
I pll one last time before bed, all goes well and mobs die, total exp gained = 2 yellow bubbles .... total gain for the day after factoring in deaths, = .25 of a yellow.....
<br />
But at least I are having fun!!!
<br />
5. Any other comments you would have about your time in Molto are welcome.
<br />
I helped kill Ragefire in skyfire mtns at level 38, was not second guessed at all due to the reputation of Molto.
<br />
Helped kill Phinny in Kedge Keep at level 48 with only two other molto bards, (think it was Scherzo and Starpoint ... memory bad but am almost sure)  was a great learning experiencee for me to see how bards can work together to take down mobs that otherwise take one or two well balanced groups of other classes.
<br />
I have learned more about the alternate ways of approching the game and had a better time playing the passed month or so with Molto than my entire 5 years playing any other character on my other servers.
<br />

<br />
Movin Tarrget
