I first started playing EQ about 2 years ago when I picked up a copy of PC Gamer that had a free 30 day trail of New Dawn.  I remember letting my 56k download the 8 hour update thinking &quot;this had better be worth the wait!&quot;
<br />
Since then I have played nearly all of the classes trying to figure out what I wanted to do.  I took a (forced) break during the 2nd Gulf War due to an RAF reserve callup, which lasted about a year.
<br />
I came back a started a Pally and made a good friend in a mage on the VS server.  Unfortunatly he was able to put in more time than I could and he was soon 20+ levels ahead of me and in a good raiding guild ( I am still trying to tempt him into making a bard<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-2.gif" border="0" alt="Big Smile" hspace="2" /> )
