			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Who are you, and why do you play in Molto Espressivo?<a name="60117"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 2 04 7:41 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>1) I started playing EQ shortly after Velios came out, 3 1/2 years ago.  My first guild ever was a very lowbie, &quot;nobody knows what they're doing so let's all work together&quot; very family-oriented guild on the Nameless.  To me, that's exactly what a guild should be like, everybody friends, actually spending time together doing stuff and having fun (NOT soloing all the time for the xp).  I've grown my own crop of characters, a 49 wizard, a 42 warrior, 34 cleric, etc.  To my friends I'm known as &quot;the man with the thousand alts&quot; Lol.  I've trained people in playing EQ several times, from EQ newbies to people that just wanted to learn t0 play (insert class here) better.  
<br />

<br />
2)  Every time I try a new class, the first thing I do is go to the class-specific web site and read as much as I possibly can, in this case EQDiva.  After reading guides and such, I made my bard on the nameless and tried to do them, I was miserable at playing a bard, lol.  Practice, practice, it was a challenge, barding was THE most concentration and skills and total-knowledge-of-the-game intensive class I've every played.  So, it became my turn to learn.  I saw the post for the bard-only guild on FV and just had to join!  I haven't looked back since.  (Well okay, I look back all the time, but Koda keeps me looking forward too, so I don't run into those blasted trees!)
<br />

<br />
3)  Of course, the drunken parties we used to have!  Playing truth or dare and me daring Ayuir to run nekked through Felwithe from one zone to the other while playing DDD (and she lived!).  All-bard (well, five and a cleric) grouping in splitpaw, most fun I've ever had, even though I died once (or twice).  Spending a week (or was it two) teaching Cantilena how to play EQ, and then how to play a bard.
<br />

<br />
4)  My typical day in molto.  I tend to do one of several things lately... say hello in guild and be afk the rest of the night (or so it seems)....  call out to see if anyone wants to group, end up running to cobolt scar to solo wyverns....  call out to see if anyone wants to group, end up working on tradeskills (trying to figure out fishing-the bait spinning side right now)...  or going on a raid of some type (not really a huge fan of raids but they're necessary at some point).
<br />

<br />
5)  I'm the self-appointed &quot;trainer&quot; of the guild, so if you ever, I mean EVER, want some help with the &quot;how to&quot; of barding, please please please just ask, save me from my own self-inflicted punishment of tradeskilling!  Hehe</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%">Koda Kyrie, skills tutor and officer of Molto Expressivo, Firiona Vie server</span></td>
